               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18320906-455-off2563-c2633" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-455-defend3653 t18320906-455-off2563 t18320906-455-verdict2567"></join>
         
               <p>2186. 
               
                  <persName id="t18320906-455-defend3653" type="defendantName">
                     JAMES 
                     THOMAS
                  <interp inst="t18320906-455-defend3653" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-defend3653" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-defend3653" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-defend3653" type="age" value="37"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18320906-455-off2563" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-off2563" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-off2563" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18320906-455-cd2564" type="crimeDate">23d of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-455-off2563 t18320906-455-cd2564"></join>, 1 waistcoat, value 4s.; 1 tablecloth, value 2s.; 1 pair of scissors, value 2s.; 1 jacket, value 1s. 6d.; 1 pair of trousers, value 1s., and 1 handkerchief, value 6d., the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18320906-455-victim3655" type="victimName">
                           Charles 
                           Goodman
                        <interp inst="t18320906-455-victim3655" type="surname" value="Goodman"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18320906-455-victim3655" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18320906-455-victim3655" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-455-off2563 t18320906-455-victim3655"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  ; and that he he had been before convicted of felony
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>CHARLES GOODMAN. I live in <placeName id="t18320906-455-crimeloc2565">Margaret-court, Oxford-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-455-crimeloc2565" type="placeName" value="Margaret-court, Oxford-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-455-crimeloc2565" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-455-off2563 t18320906-455-crimeloc2565"></join>, and am a <rs id="t18320906-455-viclabel2566" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-455-victim3655 t18320906-455-viclabel2566"></join>. I lost these things on the 23rd of August - they were worth about 12s.; they had been safe in my house the night before, and I missed them between six and seven o'clock in the morning from the back room, at the top of the house, where I work, and where my children sleep.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-455-person3656">
                  GEORGE 
                  JOHN RESTIEAUX
               <interp inst="t18320906-455-person3656" type="surname" value="JOHN RESTIEAUX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-person3656" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-person3656" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable E 49). I took the the prisoner into custody on the 23rd of August, between six and seven o'clock in the morning; he had in his basket the articles stated in the indictment; and he had, concealed in his sleeve, three keys and a purse, with 12s. 6d.; one of the keys opens the door of the house in which the prosecutor lives - it is a latch-key; I asked how he got the things, but he would not say any thing, but pretended to cry - he was particularly reserved.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-455-person3657">
                  JOHN 
                  VENNEL
               <interp inst="t18320906-455-person3657" type="surname" value="VENNEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-person3657" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-person3657" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable S 140). I have a certificate of the conviction of the prisoner, which I got from Mr. Clark's office; I was present when the prisoner was tried on the 16th of February - he is the person, and was three months in Newgate.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18320906-455-verdict2567" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-verdict2567" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 37. - <rs id="t18320906-455-punish2568" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320906-455-punish2568" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-455-defend3653 t18320906-455-punish2568"></join>
               Transported for Life
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
